 President Muhammadu Buhari has warmly felicitated with Fatai Olaniyi Adegbenro, Osi of Owu Kingdom and Baaloro of Egbaland, on his 80th birthday, on April 3, 2022. The President in a statement issued by his spokesman, Femi Adesina, joined family, friends and associates of the leader and administrator in celebrating the milestone, heralded by many years of service to the nation and humanity. President Buhari extolled Adegbenro for always putting the interest of the nation first in his undertakings, willingly counseling leaders on the right path to honour, dignity and unity of the country. “As the revered leader turns 80, the President prays for his good health and strength,” Adesina added. 